      <title>Changing Trends of Weddings</title>
      <description>&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: windowtext; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;; font-style: normal;"&gt;I have always loved attending the weddings. No matter the person is close to me or not, as attending a wedding has really a charm. You would nowhere find such fun filled ceremonies where everyone, be it the youngest or the older family member, enjoys to the fullest. The weddings are indeed the best time to celebrate the togetherness with the family.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: windowtext; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;; font-style: normal;"&gt;As the time passes, the ways to celebrate the wedding changes, and so does the customs associated with it. People always run short of time, and hence it is a great excuse for not attending the weddings. But as I do believe, the one whom you love, you will definitely spare some time from your busy schedule. The busy time table of people has been one of the main reasons why the children are unaware of the culture and also the customs of the family and like to search their partner on their own or through &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.jeevansathi.com/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: black; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;; font-style: normal;"&gt;matrimonial&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: black; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: black; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;; font-style: normal;"&gt;sites&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: windowtext; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;; font-style: normal;"&gt;No community in India is untouched with this “shortage of time” virus now. Earlier, the weddings ought to be three-four days song ceremony, and all the moments of the wedding were fully enjoyed by the family members as well as the friends. How can on miss those awesome cultural moments!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: windowtext; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;; font-style: normal;"&gt;The wedding rituals have been cut short to get rid of everything in short time. But I really think that there is need for us to revive our older traditions and get more involved with our family functions like our elders were.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: windowtext; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;; font-style: normal;"&gt;The best thing that time has brought with it is the &lt;a href="http://www.jeevansathi.com/" target="_blank"&gt;matrimonial websites&lt;/a&gt;; you can search your life partner without making any public announcement of it. Still, weddings are still fun to be a part of and some people still enjoy the feeling of togetherness with the family, after all, the wedding is all about uniting!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoSubtitle" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: windowtext; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;; font-style: normal;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Author:&lt;/b&gt; Rashmi Karan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/2471714813756673607-2288142364478814375?l=matrimonyknots.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/matrimony-knots/Matrimony_Knots-Changing_Trends_of_Weddings.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <link>http://matrimonyknots.blogspot.com/2012/04/changing-trends-of-weddings.html</link>
      <author>noreply@blogger.com (Amit Kumar Verma)</author>
