    <item>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-2471714813756673607.post-7589878306336390579</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 18 Jan 2012 06:03:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <atom:updated>2012-01-17T22:03:51.217-08:00</atom:updated>
      <category domain="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#">kerala marriage</category>
      <category domain="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#">kerala wedding culture</category>
      <category domain="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#">kerala bride</category>
      <category domain="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#">kerala wedding</category>
      <category domain="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#">kerala matrimony</category>
      <category domain="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#">kerala matrimonial</category>
      <title>Fixing of a Wedding in Kerala Matrimony</title>
      <description>&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;In India, a wedding is the biggest event for a family, which is a true reflection of social obligation, kinship, traditional value, impassioned sentiment, and economic resources. There are many traditions in India because of the large number of religions coexist. However marriage is a momentous time for all in life. Marriage unites more than just a man and a woman, it binds two families. For an individual, marriage is the greatest turning point of life, marking the transition to adulthood and provoking the sense of responsibility in everyone. The rituals and traditions of the Hindu marriage are passed from generation to generation. The wedding ceremony is one of the oldest traditions of Indian culture.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Marriages in India are not personal arrangements like western countries. It is primarily an arrangement between two families, and then the union between a man and a woman. Even today, 90% of Hindu marriages are arranged. The wedding ceremonies vary among castes and regions. However, the initial rituals of the ceremony remain similar in almost all the religions. In &lt;a href="http://www.jeevansathi.com/matrimonials/kerala-matrimonial/" target="_blank"&gt;Kerala matrimony&lt;/a&gt; the matches are found by the parents, who generally take help of match makers or online matrimonial sites. After finding the perfect match, the two families and the boy and girl meet.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The astrologers are concerned and the horoscopes of the boy and girl are matched to predict their future life. If the horoscopes have some issues that may be harmful for the future life of the couple, there are solutions too! The parents take help of their family astrologers and perform Puja to correct the positioning of stars, as per their belief. The date and time suitable for the wedding ceremony are fixed and the wedding in &lt;a href="http://www.jeevansathi.com/matrimonials/kerala-matrimonial/" target="_blank"&gt;Kerala matrimonial&lt;/a&gt; is conducted in a very simple and elegant manner.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;Author:&lt;/b&gt; Rashmi Karan&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/2471714813756673607-7589878306336390579?l=matrimonyknots.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/matrimony-knots/Matrimony_Knots-Fixing_of_a_Wedding_in_Kerala_Matrimony.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <link>http://matrimonyknots.blogspot.com/2012/01/fixing-of-wedding-in-kerala-matrimony.html</link>
      <author>noreply@blogger.com (Amit Kumar Verma)</author>
      <thr:total>0</thr:total>
